name: Care-A-Van Welcome Back Tacoma
vaccines: Janssen COVID-19 Vaccine, Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine, Pfizer-BioNTech COVID-19 Vaccine
info:
This is a multiple vaccine type clinic offering J&J as a single dose, Moderna as 1st or 2nd dose, and Pfizer as 1st or 2nd dose. Please indicate which vaccine you are seeking and if this is a 1st or 2nd dose. Please note: Johnson & Johnson and Moderna vaccine can only be administered to individuals 18 years of age or older according CDC requirements. Pfizer can be administered to youth ages 12 to 17 if accompanied by an adult who can sign a parental consent form.
**************************************************************************************
This vaccine clinic is located at Wright Park being held in collaboration with Metro Parks Tacoma the Governor’s Office, the “Washington Ready” campaign, WA Department of Health and Bird's Eye Medical. This campaign is a statewide celebration of the end to current COVID-19 restrictions and provides an opportunity for Washingtonians to celebrate the end of this chapter.  
 
For details and updates, including special announcements on the “Welcome Back, Tacoma!” event, visit cityoftacoma.org/welcomeback.

*******************************************************************************
Please let us know if you or someone you are accompanying needs assistance of any kind.  **You should also plan your visit around waiting for 15 minutes in the observation area so we can monitor for any unlikely adverse reactions to the vaccine.** Certain people with pre-identified conditions or past anaphylaxis events may be asked to wait for 30 minutes of observation.

Free language translation services are provided. Video ASL translation is also provided.
*****************************************************************************
If this is your 2nd dose please bring your vaccination card from your 1st dose. If you do not have your card you may register with and confirm proof of vaccination at https://wa.myir.net/                      
 Please do not come if you are feeling ill. Please arrive as close as possible to your scheduled time to prevent crowding that will impede appropriate social distancing. - It is best to wear clothes that will allow for access to your upper arm, just below the shoulder.
****************************************************************************
Participants are asked to enjoy this celebration responsibly by following current CDC masking requirements while in attendance.
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Walla Walla County HD- COVID Provider
vaccines: Janssen COVID-19 Vaccine, Pfizer-BioNTech COVID-19 Vaccine
info:
**THIS CLINIC IS BY APPOINTMENT ONLY FOR 1st DOSE PFIZER VACCINATIONS for all qualifying individuals aged 12 years & over. Parental/Guardian consent is required for 12 – 17 year olds, parent/guardian consent and signature can be completed on-site or in the final screen of the online registration process. Janssen (Johnson & Johnson) vaccine is also available for people 18 years and older. This clinic is at the Providence Southgate Medical Park main building (the former Walla Walla General Hospital) 1025 South 2nd Ave. Participants are advised to stay to their right as they enter the campus and proceed to the main entrance, instead of going to Urgent Care. COVID vaccine is not available in Urgent Care.
Masks are required. If you do not have a mask, one will be provided.
We look forward to seeing you. Thanks for keeping Walla Walla well.

** ESTA CLÍNICA ES CON CITA SOLAMENTE PARA LAS VACUNAS DE LA PRIMERA DOSIS DE PFIZER para personas calificadas de 12 años en Adelante.  Se requiere el consentimiento de los padres / tutores para los jóvenes de 12 - 17 años, las firmas y el consentimiento en la pantalla de registro final.  La vacuna Janssen (Johnson & Johnson) también está disponible para personas mayores de 18 años.** Esto será en el edificio principal de Providence Southgate Medical Park, (antes conocido como el Hospital General de Walla Walla)1025 Sur 2nd ave.  Se recomienda a los participantes que se mantengan a su derecha al ingresar y que se dirijan a la entrada principal, en lugar de ir a Atención de Urgencia.  La Vacuna COVID no está disponible en Atención de Urgencias. **
El cubre bocas es requerido. Si no tiene un cubre bocas, se le proporcionará una.  
Esperamos verlo. Gracias por cuidar a Walla Walla.

address: Capital Mall - 625 Black Lake Boulevard Southwest, Olympia WA, 98502
info:
This is a Pfizer vaccination event for anyone age 12 and older. 

• This is a walk-in clinic at Capital Mall located at 625 Black Lake Blvd SW, Olympia WA, 98502 for anyone age 12 and older from 12pm-8pm.  We will be located inside the mall, closest to the Sephora end of the mall and next to the Buckle store.• All minors 12 to 17 years old must receive parent or guardian consent to receive a COVID-19 vaccine. This must be done in PrepMod when registering for an appointment. Parents or guardians do not have to be present at the time of vaccination if they signed the consent form online during registration. • Please bring a form of identification with you to your appointment - ID card, passport, or other document with your name and birthday on it. • Wear a short-sleeved shirt, but dress with layers if necessary. • Waiting at least 15 minutes after vaccination is required.
